<item>
            <title>[LU-19097] kernel update [RHEL 9.6 5.14.0-570.21.1.el9_6]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19097</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: net: gso: fix ownership in __udp_gso_segment (CVE-2025-21926)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: vlan: enforce underlying device type (CVE-2025-21920)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: xsk: fix an integer overflow in xp_create_and_assign_umem() (CVE-2025-21997)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: net: fix geneve_opt length integer overflow (CVE-2025-22055)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: ext4: fix OOB read when checking dotdot dir (CVE-2025-37785)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: wifi: ath12k: Fix invalid data access in ath12k_dp_rx_h_undecap_nwifi (CVE-2025-37943)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---9/x86_64/RHSA-2025:8643&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/product/479/ver=/rhel---9/x86_64/RHSA-2025:8643&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
